text.section:
The articles of amendment shall set forth:
The name of the association;
The amendment adopted;
A statement setting forth the date of the meeting of the board at which the amendment or amendments were approved; that the meeting was duly called and that a quorum was present; and that a resolution approving the proposed amendment, or amendments, received an affirmative vote of not less than two-thirds (2/3) of the members of the board present and voting at such meeting;
A statement setting forth the date of the meeting of the members of the association at which the amendment was adopted; that the meeting was duly called and that a quorum was present; and that such amendment received an affirmative vote of not less than a majority of the votes entitled to be cast by members present in person, or by proxy (if permitted by the bylaws), and voting at such meeting.
